Bayelsa State Government has announced fresh match-winning bonuses and allowances for players and officials of its premier league side, Bayelsa United FC, as the 2022 Nigerian National League (NNL) season heats up. The state Deputy Governor, Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, made this known at a special dinner organised to motivate the players, technical crew and coaching staff of the team in Yenagoa on Saturday. He specified that the team would receive N1.5m for every league game won in the current season while each goal-scorer would be given N200,000. CAF Confederation Cup: Diri Rewards Bayelsa United With N14m,… Excitement As 3SC Back In ‘Premiership’ Ewhrudjakpo further said that for each goal scored, the first assist would get N150,000 while the second and third assists would get N100, 000 each. He thanked the Bayelsa United team players and officials for making the state proud by flying the state’s flag at the continental level in 2021 after failing to do so for several years. Ewhrudjakpo also appreciated the team for winning the 2021 Aiteo Cup and charged them to win the league trophy this year. According to him, both the state government and the management of Bayelsa United had to cover up the gaps which denied the Yenagoa-based side laurels in their last continental outing. The Deputy Chief of Staff, Deputy Governor’s office, Alex Dumbo explained that the dinner was specifically put together to enable the deputy governor to interact freely with players and officials of the team. POLL He said the dinner was also to serve as a platform to motivate them to fly high in the ongoing football season. The Chairman of Bayelsa United, Ebiki Timitimi, thanked the deputy governor for organising the special dinner for the team. He assured the government that the team would secure the much-needed victories in their subsequent league matches beginning from their home game against visiting Rocket 1 FC of Uyo, Akwa Ibom State.